# Accessibility and UX

## Touch Targets
- Minimum touch target size: 44x44 points
- Use `TouchableOpacity` with `activeOpacity={0.7}` for visual feedback
- Provide adequate spacing between interactive elements

## Visual Feedback
- Use consistent `activeOpacity` values
- Implement proper loading states with `ActivityIndicator`
- Show clear error states with helpful messages
- Use color changes for interactive states

## Text Accessibility
- Use semantic text variants: `variant="headlineLarge"`, `variant="bodyMedium"`
- Ensure sufficient color contrast
- Use `numberOfLines` and `ellipsizeMode` for text truncation
- Provide descriptive text for icons and buttons

## Navigation UX
- Use consistent navigation patterns with `router.push()`
- Provide clear back navigation
- Use proper screen titles and headers
- Implement breadcrumbs where appropriate

## Form UX
- Use proper input types and validation
- Provide clear error messages
- Use consistent form layouts
- Implement proper keyboard handling

## Loading and Empty States
- Always show loading indicators for async operations
- Provide helpful empty states with clear actions
- Use skeleton loading for better perceived performance
- Implement proper error boundaries

## Animation Guidelines
- Use `Animated` API for smooth transitions
- Keep animations under 300ms for responsiveness
- Use `useNativeDriver: true` when possible for performance
- Provide subtle feedback animations

## Color and Contrast
- Use high contrast colors for text
- Ensure interactive elements are clearly distinguishable
- Use consistent color meanings (red for errors, green for success)
- Test with accessibility tools

## Screen Reader Support
- Use proper semantic elements
- Provide meaningful labels for interactive elements
- Use `accessibilityLabel` and `accessibilityHint` when needed
- Test with screen readers